1.	Define SQL Server Instance.
A). An sql server instances is a separate installation of sql server that runs as its own servce
    and manages its own databases, security and configuration settings
    Simple : one computer can run multiple sql server instances
    each instances works independently

2.	What does the master database contain?
A). The master database contains
        sys level information
        login accounts
        configuration settings
        information about all databases
        sys stored procedures
    # if master is damaged sql server wont start properly.

3.	What is the model database’s function?
A). The model database acts as a tenplate
    whenever a new satabases is creates , sql server copies structure from the model database
    if you create table in model every new database will automatically have them .
